The paper deals with communication over wireless links in the presence of an adversary, which is a common problem in the field of information theory (cs.IT). The use of game theory to model the interaction between the transmitter/receiver and the jammer suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of adaptive transmission parameters, which is a topic in the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The presence of an adversary and the need to protect against jamming attacks suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the use of optimization techniques to find optimal strategies for the transmitter and jammer suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
